The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 The Emami group will invest Rs 2,000 crore in Chhattisgarh within the next three years, company sources said. The company is planning to set up a 4-milliontonne cement plant and also a 100-mw power plant in the state with a total investment of Rs 1,600 crore, they said. The company is also investing Rs 150 crore to set up a bio-diesel plant in the state. It plans to construct a 500-bed hospital near the state capital.

 Germany-based chemical company LANXESS has recorded a double-digit sales growth in India to 185.5 million euros. The management board and supervisory board of the company will seek shareholders approval at the annual meeting on May 31 to pay a dividend of 0.25 euro per share. 

 Thomas Cook (India) Ltds net profit in the 14-month period ended December 31, 2006 has increased 8 per cent to Rs 36 crore from Rs 28.5 crore. Revenues during the period increased to Rs 234.7 crore from Rs 130.8 crore. The board has proposed a dividend of 50 per cent against 37.5 per cent declared in the previous year.

 The Madhya Pradesh Housing Board has signed two agreements with the Indian Infrastructure Initiative, a facility created by IDFC and Feedback Ventures. Indian Infrastructure Initiative will conceptualise the projects, manage the process of identification and selection of private sector partners.

 Tata Teleservices Ltd has launched Motofone F3c on the CDMA platform in the country. The device is based on the Qualcomm Single-Chip chipset family. The phone is priced at Rs 1,699, and comes with a starter pack of Go XTRA.

 DaimlerChrysler has unveiled two models in the Indian market the diesel-based S-Class and the premium Mercedes-Benz CL-Class. The S-Class diesel model, S320, is priced at Rs 70 lakh and the Mercedes-Benz CL-Class is priced in the range of Rs 1.2 to 1.7 crore.

 Chabria InfoTech has been appointed the exclusive partner for the media and entertainment division of Autodesk in the eastern region. Chabria InfoTech will promote Maya and 3D Max software.

 HCL Infosystems Ltd has launched a range of eco-efficient consumer and business notebooks compliant with the restriction of hazardous substances (RoHS) directive. 

 Woodland has launched a range of formal footwear for men. The range is priced between Rs 4,995 and Rs 7,995 and is available in shades of brown and black.

